original: Ahlstrand, Torsten Herbert, kyrkoadjunkt, Borås, f. 7/1/07 i Fässberg, Gbgs o. Boh. 1., av disp. Harald A. o. Frida Larsdotter. G. 35 m. Lizzie Tenelius. Barn: Lars f. 36, Jan Torsten 38, Harald 39. — Studrex. i Gbg 25, fil. kand. 28, fil. lic. 30, teol. kand. 32, prästv. f. Skara stift 33. V. past. i Norra Ving 33-34, kyrkoadj. i Borås fr. 34. Styr iled. i fören. Hemgården, Borås, fr. 43, led. av förs:-hemskomm. fr. 41, av kyrkofullm. fr. 46, av fritidsberedn., av namnberedn., styr:led. i Borås-Sjuhäradsbygd. konstfören. 37-43, konstkrit. i Västg.-Demokr. sed. 43. Sign.: T. A. Skr.: Manfred Flyckt (42).
translated: Ahlstrand, Torsten Herbert, church assistant, Borås, b. 7/1/07 in Fässberg, Gothenburg and Bohus County, son of Harald A. and Frida Larsdotter. Married to Lizzie Tenelius in 1935 and they have three sons: Lars b. 1936, Jan Torsten b. 1938, and Harald b. 1939. He studied at the University of Gothenburg from 1925-1932 and then at the Faculty of Theology where he received his ordination in 1933 for the diocese of Skara. He worked as a vicar in Norra Ving from 1933-1934 and then as a church assistant in Borås from 1934 onwards. He was a board member of the society Hemgården in Borås from 1943, a member of the parish home committee from 1941, a member of the church board from 1946, a member of the leisure committee, a member of the naming committee, and a board member of the Borås-Sjuhäradsbygd art society from 1937-1943. He was also an art critic for Västgöta-Demokraten since 1943. His signature is T.A. He has written the book Manfred Flyckt (1942).
